237
01:09:23,566 --> 01:09:26,199
<b>often downplayed or outright denied.</b>

238
01:09:26,933 --> 01:09:29,399
<b>Getting the story right on Stalin is more</b>

239
01:09:29,399 --> 01:09:31,066
<b>than just an academic exercise.</b>

240
01:09:31,866 --> 01:09:34,899
<b>It is a vital lesson in how power,</b>

241
01:09:34,899 --> 01:09:37,833
<b>paranoia and a disregard for the truth</b>

242
01:09:37,833 --> 01:09:41,033
<b>can lead to unimaginable suffering.</b>

243
01:09:42,333 --> 01:09:44,433
<b>The most terrifying thing about these</b>

244
01:09:44,433 --> 01:09:46,466
<b>lies is not that they were told.</b>

245
01:09:47,333 --> 01:09:48,800
<b>It's that they were believed</b>

246
01:09:48,800 --> 01:09:51,966
<b>and still are in some places.</b>

247
01:09:52,833 --> 01:09:54,166
<b>Believing Stalin's myths</b>

248
01:09:54,166 --> 01:09:56,866
<b>once cost millions of lives.</b>

249
01:09:57,399 --> 01:09:58,433
<b>Believing them now</b>

250
01:09:58,433 --> 01:10:00,199
<b>could cost millions more.</b>

